Thema befassen, ob in Politik, Unternehmen, als Investoren, Journalisten oder interessierte Bürger, ist der Band eine Pflichtlektüre für das Verständnis des Wechselspiels von Mensch und Natur.  aThe `sustainability zeroline' is the first clear benchmark for sustainable practices, and represents a clear call to rethink sustainability. Based on an analysis of the ecologically destructive consequences of resource-intensive economics and the central insight that the conflict between growth and planetary limits becomes practical in the opposition between private goods and the commons, J. Daniel Dahm introduces the benchmark for a life-serving economy. For everyone who deals seriously with this topic, whether it is in politics, business, as investors, journalists or interested citizens, this volume is compulsory reading for understanding the interplay of humanity and nature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aClimate change. 0aEnvironmental policy. 0aHuman ecology. 0aSocial responsibility of business. 0aSustainable development. 4aCorporate Social Responsibility. 4aHumanökologie. 4aKlimawandel. 4aNachhaltigkeit. 4aNatur. 4aPolitik. 4aRating. 4aSoziologie. 4aUmweltpolitik. 4aWirtschaft. 4aZukunftsfähigkeit. 4aÖkologie. 4aÖkonomie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Human Geography.2bisacsh  aClimate Change.  aCorporate Social Responsibility.  aEcology.  aEconomy.  aEnvironmental Policy.  aHuman Ecology.  aNature.  aPolitics.  aRating.  aSociology.  aSustainability.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019z9783110606386oZDB-23-DPM40uhttps:/